description: ShadowLink configures asynchronous data replication from a source Redpanda cluster to a shadow (destination) cluster. The link is configuration on the shadow cluster — no infrastructure is provisioned. Each broker in the shadow cluster runs internal replication tasks that pull from the source over the standard Kafka API. The shadow cluster must have `enable_shadow_linking=true` set in its `cluster_configuration.custom_properties_json`.
attributes:
    - name: allow_deletion
      description: Allows deletion of the shadow link. Defaults to false.
    - name: client_options
      description: ShadowLinkClientOptions configures the Kafka client connection settings.
      attributes:
        - name: authentication_configuration
          description: 'Authentication config. Supports: * SASL/SCRAM * SASL/PLAIN'
          attributes:
            - name: plain_configuration
              description: PLAIN settings
              attributes:
                - name: password
                  description: Password
                - name: password_set
                  description: Indicates that the password has been set
                - name: password_set_at
                  description: Timestamp of when the password was last set - only valid if password_set is true
                - name: username
                  description: PLAIN username
            - name: scram_configuration
              description: SCRAM settings
              attributes:
                - name: password
                  description: Password
                - name: password_set
                  description: Indicates that the password has been set
                - name: password_set_at
                  description: Timestamp of when the password was last set - only valid if password_set is true
                - name: scram_mechanism
                  description: '- SCRAM_MECHANISM_SCRAM_SHA_256: SCRAM-SHA-256 - SCRAM_MECHANISM_SCRAM_SHA_512: SCRAM-SHA-512'
                - name: username
                  description: SCRAM username
        - name: bootstrap_servers
          description: Bootstrap servers for the source cluster. Required if source Redpanda ID is not provided.
        - name: client_id
          description: Client ID for the connection.
        - name: connection_timeout_ms
          description: Connection timeout in milliseconds (defaults to 1000ms if 0).
        - name: effective_connection_timeout_ms
          description: The effective connection timeout in milliseconds
        - name: effective_fetch_max_bytes
          description: The effective fetch max bytes
        - name: effective_fetch_min_bytes
          description: The effective fetch min bytes
        - name: effective_fetch_partition_max_bytes
          description: The effective fetch partition max bytes
        - name: effective_fetch_wait_max_ms
          description: The effective fetch wait max in milliseconds
        - name: effective_metadata_max_age_ms
          description: The effective metadata max age in milliseconds
        - name: effective_retry_backoff_ms
          description: The effective retry backoff in milliseconds
        - name: fetch_max_bytes
          description: Maximum bytes to fetch (defaults to 20971520 bytes / 20 MiB if 0).
        - name: fetch_min_bytes
          description: Minimum bytes to fetch (defaults to 5242880 bytes / 5 MiB if 0).
        - name: fetch_partition_max_bytes
          description: Maximum bytes per partition to fetch (defaults to 1048576 bytes / 1 MiB if 0).
        - name: fetch_wait_max_ms
          description: Maximum time to wait for fetch requests in milliseconds (defaults to 500ms if 0).
        - name: metadata_max_age_ms
          description: Metadata refresh interval in milliseconds (defaults to 10000ms if 0).
        - name: retry_backoff_ms
          description: Retry backoff in milliseconds (defaults to 100ms if 0).
        - name: source_cluster_id
          description: Source cluster ID.
        - name: tls_settings
          description: TLSSettings configures TLS encryption.
          attributes:
            - name: ca
              description: The CA certificate for TLS.
            - name: cert
              description: Cert is the certificate for TLS. Key and Cert are optional but if one is provided, then both must be provided.
            - name: do_not_set_sni_hostname
              description: Do not set SNI hostname.
            - name: enabled
              description: Enable TLS.
            - name: key
              description: The private key for TLS. Key and Cert are optional but if one is provided, then both must be provided.
    - name: consumer_offset_sync_options
      description: Options for syncing consumer offsets
      attributes:
        - name: effective_interval
          description: The effective interval for the task
        - name: group_filters
          description: The filters
          attributes:
            - name: filter_type
              description: '- FILTER_TYPE_INCLUDE: Include the items that match the filter - FILTER_TYPE_EXCLUDE: Exclude the items that match the filter'
            - name: name
              description: The resource name, or "*" Note if "*", must be the _only_ character and `pattern_type` must be `PATTERN_TYPE_LITERAL`
            - name: pattern_type
              description: '- PATTERN_TYPE_LITERAL: Must match the filter exactly - PATTERN_TYPE_PREFIX: Will match anything that starts with filter - PATTERN_TYPE_PREFIXED: Will match anything that starts with filter'
        - name: interval
          description: Sync interval If 0 provided, defaults to 30 seconds
        - name: paused
          description: Allows user to pause the consumer offset sync task. If paused, then the task will enter the 'paused' state and not sync consumer offsets from the source cluster
    - name: id
      description: Shadow link ID.
    - name: name
      description: 'Human-readable name for the shadow link. Must be unique. Must follow Kubernetes DNS-1123 subdomain naming convention: - lowercase alphanumeric characters, hyphens allowed - must start and end with alphanumeric character - maximum 63 characters. Length must be at most 63. Must match pattern `^[a-z0-9]([-a-z0-9]*[a-z0-9])?$`.'
    - name: reason
      description: Reason provides additional context for the current state.
    - name: schema_registry_sync_options
      description: Options for how the Schema Registry is synced.
      attributes:
        - name: shadow_schema_registry_topic
          description: 'Shadow the entire source cluster''s Schema Registry byte-for-byte. If set, the Shadow Link will attempt to add the `_schemas` topic to the list of Shadow Topics as long as: 1. The `_schemas` topic exists on the source cluster 2. The `_schemas` topic does not exist on the shadow cluster, or it is empty. If either of the above conditions are _not_ met, then the `_schemas` topic will _not_ be shadowed by this cluster. Unsetting this flag will _not_ remove the `_schemas` topic from shadowing if it has already been added. Once made a shadow topic, the `_schemas` topic will be replicated byte-for-byte. To stop shadowing the `_schemas` topic, unset this field, then either fail-over the topic or delete it.'
    - name: security_sync_options
      description: Options for syncing security settings
      attributes:
        - name: acl_filters
          description: ACL filters
          attributes:
            - name: access_filter
              description: Filter an ACL based on its access
              attributes:
                - name: host
                  description: The host to match. If not set, will default to match all hosts with the specified `operation` and `permission_type`. Note that the asterisk `*` is literal and matches hosts that are set to `*`
                - name: operation
                  description: The ACL operation to match
                - name: permission_type
                  description: ACL permission types
                - name: principal
                  description: The name of the principal, if not set will default to match all principals with the specified `operation` and `permission_type`
            - name: resource_filter
              description: A filter to match ACLs for resources
              attributes:
                - name: name
                  description: Name, if not given will default to match all items in `resource_type`. Note that asterisk `*` is literal and matches resource ACLs that are named `*`
                - name: pattern_type
                  description: '- ACL_PATTERN_ANY: Wildcard to match any pattern - ACL_PATTERN_LITERAL: Match a literal string - ACL_PATTERN_PREFIXED: Match a prefix - ACL_PATTERN_PREFIX: Match a prefix - ACL_PATTERN_MATCH: Match serves as a catch-all for all the names of a topic the principal is authorized to access'
                - name: resource_type
                  description: '- ACL_RESOURCE_ANY: Wildcard for selecting any ACL resource - ACL_RESOURCE_CLUSTER: Cluster wide resource - ACL_RESOURCE_GROUP: Consumer group resource - ACL_RESOURCE_TOPIC: Topic resource - ACL_RESOURCE_TXN_ID: Transaction ID resource - ACL_RESOURCE_SR_SUBJECT: Schema Registry subject resource - ACL_RESOURCE_SR_REGISTRY: Schema Registry wide resource - ACL_RESOURCE_SR_ANY: Wildcard to match any SR ACL resource'
        - name: effective_interval
          description: The effective interval for the task
        - name: interval
          description: Sync interval If 0 provided, defaults to 30 seconds
        - name: paused
          description: Allows user to pause the security settings sync task. If paused, then the task will enter the 'paused' state and will not sync security settings from the source cluster
    - name: shadow_redpanda_id
      description: Shadow Redpanda cluster ID where the shadow link is created. This ID is immutable.
    - name: source_redpanda_id
      description: Source Redpanda ID
    - name: state
      description: State represents the lifecycle state of a shadow link.
    - name: topic_metadata_sync_options
      description: Options for syncing topic metadata
      attributes:
        - name: auto_create_shadow_topic_filters
          description: List of filters that indicate which topics should be automatically created as shadow topics on the shadow cluster. This only controls automatic creation of shadow topics and does not effect the state of the mirror topic once it is created. Literal filters for __consumer_offsets, _redpanda.audit_log and _schemas will be rejected as well as prefix filters to match topics prefixed with _redpanda or __redpanda. Wildcard `*` is permitted only for literal filters and will _not_ match any topics that start with _redpanda or __redpanda. If users wish to shadow topics that start with _redpanda or __redpanda, they should provide a literal filter for those topics.
          attributes:
            - name: filter_type
              description: '- FILTER_TYPE_INCLUDE: Include the items that match the filter - FILTER_TYPE_EXCLUDE: Exclude the items that match the filter'
            - name: name
              description: The resource name, or "*" Note if "*", must be the _only_ character and `pattern_type` must be `PATTERN_TYPE_LITERAL`
            - name: pattern_type
              description: '- PATTERN_TYPE_LITERAL: Must match the filter exactly - PATTERN_TYPE_PREFIX: Will match anything that starts with filter - PATTERN_TYPE_PREFIXED: Will match anything that starts with filter'
        - name: effective_interval
          description: The effective interval for the task
        - name: exclude_default
          description: If this is true, then only the properties listed in `synced_shadow_topic_properties` will be synced.
        - name: interval
          description: How often to sync metadata If 0 provided, defaults to 30 seconds
        - name: paused
          description: Allows user to pause the topic sync task. If paused, then the task will enter the 'paused' state and not sync topics or their properties from the source cluster
        - name: start_at_earliest
          description: Start at the earliest offset in the partition.
        - name: start_at_latest
          description: Start at the latest offset in the partition.
        - name: start_at_timestamp
          description: Enables data replication from the first offset on the source topic/partition where the record's timestamp is at or after the specified timestamp.
        - name: synced_shadow_topic_properties
          description: 'The following properties are not allowed to be replicated and adding them to this list will result in an error: - `redpanda.remote.readreplica` - `redpanda.remote.recovery` - `redpanda.remote.allowgaps` - `redpanda.virtual.cluster.id` - `redpanda.leaders.preference` - `redpanda.cloud_topic.enabled` This list is a list of properties in addition to the default properties that will be synced. See `exclude_default`.'
